The beginner slope. Marked clearly by the ski lift in #main-basin that leads up here, a sign that straight up says "Beginner's Slope" is there. Red Flags showing the path down are accompanied by bright lights that seem to turn on at night. The path down is clear of any trees or obstructions. It's really just, as the name suggests, a place for beginners to start. The slope isn't very inclined either, and if you were to fall, you would be gently let down by the snow. The end of the slope opens at the #main-basin, as all the other slopes do. At the top of the hill, nothing of note is here. It's a wide, open area for people to ride down.
